>(with Brains)</small>\n| \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2014\n| ''Full Range''\n|-\n|| 2014\n|align=\"left\"| \"Right Back\"<br/><small>(with Dr Meaker)</small>\n| 151 || 40 || 15 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013<br />|| \u2014\n| ''Dirt & Soul''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 2019\n|align=\"left\"| \"Up2U\" <br/><small>(with The Stanton Warriors)</small>\n| -\n| -\n| -\n| -\n| -\n| -\n| -\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{N/A|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"| \"Orange Heart\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/orange-heart-feat-sian-evans-single/1470322998 |title=Orange Heart (feat. Sian Evans) - Single by Headhunterz on Apple Music |website=iTunes Store |accessdate=28 July 2019}}</ref> <br/><small>(with [[Headhunterz]])</small>\n| -\n| -\n| -\n| -\n| -\n| -\n| -\n|-\n| colspan=\"10\" style=\"font-size:85%\"| \"\u2014\" denotes a recording that did not chart or was not released.\n\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://sian-evans.com Official website]\n* [https://www.facebook.com/sianevansuk Facebook page]\n* [https://twitter.com/sianevansuk Twitter]\n\n{{Kosheen}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Evans, Sian}}\n[[Category:1971 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:English dance musicians]]\n[[Category:Welsh female singers]]\n[[Category:English singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:English female singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:21st-century English singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Welsh singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century English women singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the author|Si\u00e2n Evans}}\n{{EngvarB|date=September 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2017}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Sian Evans\n| image            = Kosheen Sian Evans Wien2008.jpg\n| alt              = \n| caption          = In Vienna, 2008\n| image_size       = \n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = Sian Evans\n| alias            = \n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1971|10|09}}\n| death_date       = \n| origin           = [[Caerphilly]], Wales\n| instrument       = \n| genre            = [[Trip hop]], [[drum and bass]], rock, [[synthpop]], [[Breakbeat]], [[Dubstep]], [[Electro (music)|Electro]], [[Trance music|Trance]]\n| occupation       = Singer, songwriter\n| years_active     = 1997\u2013present\n| label            = [[Ministry of Sound]], [[Moksha Records]], [[Universal Music Group]], [[Sony BMG Music Entertainment]]\n| associated_acts  = [[Kosheen]], [[DJ Fresh]], [[Roger Shah]], [[Jody Wisternoff]], [[Dino Psaras]], [[Chicane (musician)|Chicane]], Dr. Meaker, Jolyon Petch, Brains, Martin Eyerer, Paul Hazendonk, Bent, Lee Dagger\n| website          = [http://sian-evans.com www.sian-evans.com]\n}}\n\n'''Sian Evans''' (born 9 October 1971) is a [[Welsh people|Welsh]] singer.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/sian-evans-celebrates-no1-hit-1820711 | work = [[Wales Online]] | title = Sian Evans celebrates No.1 hit with DJ Fresh}}</ref> Throughout the 2000s, she was [[front woman]] and singer-songwriter of the band [[Kosheen]], a [[Trip hop|trip-hop]]/[[drum & bass]] group that, during that decade, placed two albums within the Top Ten of the [[UK Albums Chart]]. She has also joined a list of Welsh artists to have topped the [[UK singles chart]] with collaboration on the track '[[Louder (DJ Fresh song)|Louder]]' with [[DJ Fresh]]. Kosheen disbanded in 2016.\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Studio albums with Kosheen===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:250px;\"| Album details\n!colspan=\"9\"| Peak chart positions\n!rowspan=\"2\"| [[List of music recording certifications|Certifications]]\n|-\n!style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"|[[UK Albums Chart|UK]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artists/ |title=Official Charts Company \u2013 Kosheen |publisher=[[Official Charts Company]] |date=9 April 2012 |acces